==English==

===Etymology===
Latin '''per se''', by itself, from ''[[per]]'', by or through, and ''[[se]]'', itself, himself, herself or themselves.

===Adverb===
'''''[[per]] [[se]]'''''
#By itself; without consideration of [[extraneous]] factors.

====Usage Notes====
Because this is a Latin phrase, it is usually italicized when written.  

It does not mean "for example". Instead, "e.g." which is the abbreviation for the Latin phrase ''exempli gratis'' meaning "example gift" is closer in meaning to "for example".  See http://www.wsu.edu/~brians/errors/e.g.html and http://www.wsu.edu/~brians/errors/per.html

====Translations====
*Finnish: sinänsä
*German: per se
*Icelandic: [[í sjálfu sér]], [[út af]] [[fyrir]] [[sig]]
*Spanish: per se

